Defendant Michael J Ramirez-Colon in court with attorney Peter M Wolff.  Lesli S Boese appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty on count #1 of the amended information.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 MONTHS JAIL;
TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Continue to work on obtaining GED/HSED;
*Agent to determine all other conditions they deem appropriate;
*Perform 20 hours community service (support the 180 Juvenile Diversion Program @ a rate of $10.00 per hour to offset costs/buy money).

RESTITUTION:   $750.00 (Buy Money to Waukesha County Metro Drug Unit to be paid as a condition of probation - to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SAMPLE/SURCHARGE: waived based on date of violation. 

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.
